

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title> Sweating_case_sheet_part</title>
    <link id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>


    <div class="General">
        <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: EXCESSIVE SWEATING</h3>
        
            <!-- S: Site -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Where on your body do you notice the sweating the most? Is it all over, or in specific places like your hands, feet, or armpits?"</span>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>GENERALIZED (all over):</b> <span class="endocrine">Endocrine causes (Thyroid, Menopause)</span>, <span class="infectious">Infection</span>, <span class="oncology">Malignancy</span>, <span class="pharmacology">Medications</span></li>
                    <li><b>LOCALIZED / FOCAL:</b>
                        <ul>
                            <li class="derma">Palms, Soles, Axillae -> Primary Focal Hyperhidrosis</li>
                            <li class="cns">Face (while eating) -> Gustatory sweating (Frey's Syndrome)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <!-- O: Onset -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
                <span class="verbal">"When did you first notice this excessive sweating? Was it a sudden change or has it been gradual?"</span>
                 <ul>
                    <li>Since puberty -> Suggests primary focal hyperhidrosis</li>
                    <li>Recent onset -> Suggests a secondary cause (new illness, medication)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <!-- D: Duration -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
                <span class="verbal">"How long has this been a problem for you?"</span>
            </li>

            <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>: Aggravating & Relieving Factors</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Does anything seem to trigger the sweating, like stress or certain foods?"</span>
            </li>

            <!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>: Character (Timing & Triggers)</span>
                <span class="verbal">"This is a key question: when does the sweating happen? Is it mainly at night, during the day, or in specific situations?"</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="h3 oncology infectious endocrine emergency"><b>NIGHT SWEATS</b>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>"Drenching" sweats?</b> (Requiring changing of clothes or bedsheets) -> This is a B-Symptom.</li>
                            <li>Associated with fever? -> <b class="infectious">Infection (TB, HIV, Endocarditis)</b></li>
                            <li>Associated with weight loss? -> <b class="oncology">Lymphoma, Leukemia</b>, <b class="infectious">TB</b></li>
                            <li>Associated with hot flushes? -> <b class="endocrine gynob">Menopause</b></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li class="h3 General"><b>DAYTIME SWEATING</b>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Episodic / Paroxysmal? -> <b class="endocrine emergency">Pheochromocytoma</b>, <b class="psychiatric">Panic Attack</b></li>
                            <li>Associated with eating? -> <b class="cns">Gustatory sweating</b></li>
                            <li>Constant feeling of being hot and sweaty? -> <b class="endocrine">Hyperthyroidism</b></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <!-- R: Radiation -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Radiation</span>
                <span class="verbal">(Not applicable)</span>
            </li>
            
            <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>: Associated Symptoms</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Along with the sweating, have you experienced any other symptoms like fever, weight loss, or palpitations?"</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="h3 oncology infectious">CONSTITUTIONAL ("B SYMPTOMS")
                        <ul>
                           <li class="oncology infectious">Unexplained Fever</li>
                           <li class="oncology infectious">Drenching Night Sweats</li>
                           <li class="oncology">Unexplained Weight Loss</li>
                           <li class="oncology">Lymph node swelling (lymphadenopathy)?</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li class="h3 endocrine">ENDOCRINE
                        <ul>
                           <li class="endocrine cvs">Palpitations, anxiety, tremor, diarrhea, heat intolerance -> <b class="endocrine">Hyperthyroidism</b></li>
                           <li class="endocrine cvs emergency">Episodic headache, palpitations, and sweating -> <b class="endocrine emergency">Pheochromocytoma Triad</b></li>
                           <li class="endocrine">Hot flushes, menstrual changes -> <b class="endocrine gynob">Menopause</b></li>
                           <li class="endocrine">Sweating during hunger spells -> <b class="endocrine">Hypoglycemia</b></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                     <li class="h3 cvs">CARDIOVASCULAR
                        <ul>
                           <li class="cvs emergency">Associated with chest pain or shortness of breath -> <b class="cvs emergency">Acute Coronary Syndrome</b></li>
                           <li class="cvs">Orthopnea, paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnea -> <b class="cvs">Heart Failure</b></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                     <li class="h3 infectious">INFECTIOUS
                        <ul>
                           <li class="infectious respiratory">Chronic cough, hemoptysis, travel/contact history -> <b class="infectious">Tuberculosis (TB)</b></li>
                           <li class="infectious">High-risk behaviors, other infections -> <b class="infectious">HIV</b></li>
                           <li class="infectious">New heart murmur, IV drug use -> <b class="infectious">Endocarditis</b></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            <!-- P: Progression -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Progression</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Has the sweating been getting worse over time?"</span>
            </li>

            <!-- P: Pattern -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Is there any pattern to the sweating throughout the day or month?"</span>
            </li>

            <!-- E: Effect on life -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect on Life</span>
                <span class="verbal">"How has this sweating been impacting your life? For example, your work, social activities, or sleep?"</span>
                 <ul>
                    <li>Social embarrassment / avoidance</li>
                    <li>Need to change clothes frequently</li>
                    <li>Disrupted sleep</li>
                    <li>Difficulty with tasks (e.g., gripping objects if palmar)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <!-- R: Red Flags -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red Flags</span>
                <span class="verbal">"I'm just going to summarize the key warning signs I'm looking for."</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="oncology infectious emergency">The "B-Symptoms": Drenching night sweats, unexplained fever, significant weight loss.</li>
                    <li class="cvs emergency">Sweating associated with chest pain or severe shortness of breath.</li>
                    <li class="endocrine emergency">Episodic sweating with severe headaches and palpitations.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <!-- S: Scale -->
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity / Bother Scale</span>
                <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how much does this sweating bother you and interfere with your life?"</span>
            </li>
            
    </div>
    



    <script src="harsha_iframe_youtube_player.js"></script>
